cause.description:
St Peter's Hospice...
- is THE Bristol hospice with buildings at Knowle and Brentry, 
- provides specialist care and support to around 1600 local people with an incurable illness every year, as well as supporting their families and children; 
- is a highly specialised service offering two In-patient units, two Day Hospices, a Lymphoedema clinic, Physio and Occupational Therapists, a Chaplain and an experienced Social Work team. In addition we have an Education Department offering professional training in palliative care and associated subjects; 
- is community based - our specialist nurses help care for the majority of our patients in their own homes; 
- is dependent on the community and businesses of Bristol for £4 million of funding every year. 

NOTE.  Donations made through this page go to Amnesty International.  Please go to http://www.stpetershospice.org/ if you wish to donate to St Peter's Hospice (I wasn't able to select a UK charity)

1. Free specialist palliative care should be available to Bristol's community.

2. Free respite support should be available to the family and carers of the terminally ill.

3. The hospice isn't contained within the hospice buildings;  based in, serving and funded by the community.
